        "---\n",
        "title: \"Safety-Critical Time Series Forecasting with spotforecast2 and spotforecast2-safe: A Hardened Approach to Production Machine Learning\"\n",
        "authors:\n",
        "  - name: Thomas Bartz-Beielstein\n",
        "    roles: writing\n",
        "    corresponding: true\n",
        "    affiliation: \"Department of Computational Intelligence, TH Köln\"\n",
        "date: \"February 7, 2026\"\n",
        "eval: true\n",
        "format:\n",
        "  html:\n",
        "    toc: true\n",
        "    number-sections: true\n",
        "abstract: |\n",
        "  Time series forecasting has become indispensable in safety-critical applications such as energy grids, financial systems, and autonomous control. However, existing machine learning libraries often prioritize generality and extensibility over determinism and auditability. We introduce spotforecast2 and spotforecast2-safe, two complementary Python packages built upon the skforecast foundation for reliable time series prediction. The spotforecast2 library provides a feature-rich environment for research and development, intelligently orchestrating hyperparameter tuning and model selection. The spotforecast2-safe package represents a deliberately minimized, hardened core suitable for safety-critical production environments, featuring zero dead code, deterministic transformations, and explicit fail-safe semantics. We demonstrate that the skforecast-based approach offers substantial advantages over competing libraries such as darts, particularly regarding dependency management and predictability. Both packages implement a systematic hardening strategy that reduces the attack surface while maintaining mathematical rigor and regulatory alignment with emerging standards such as the EU AI Act. This report outlines the architectural principles, design goals, and practical implications of these systems for building trustworthy machine learning pipelines in high-risk domains.\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "# spotforecast2 entso-e {#sec-code-spotforecast2-entsoe}\n",
        "\n",
        "This reference implementation demonstrates a safety-critical forecasting workflow using `spotforecast2` and `spotforecast2-safe` on ENTSO-E data. The pipeline is designed for determinism, auditability, and fail-safe operation.\n",
        "\n",
        "The workflow executes in the following phases:\n",
        "\n",
        "1.  **Data Acquisition**: Secure retrieving and merging of energy load data.\n",
        "2.  **Configuration & Model Selection**: Centralized configuration of hyperparameters, feature engineering, and automated tuning strategies.\n",
        "3.  **Model Orchestration & Training**: Fail-safe model training with automatic refitting policies.\n",
        "4.  **Predictive Analytics & Visualization**: Generation of validated prediction packages and interactive reports.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Required Packages"
