        "## Configuration & Model Selection\n",
        "\n",
        "Deterministic configuration is enforced via the `ConfigEntsoe` class. This ensures that all components of the pipeline (training, prediction, feature engineering) share a single source of truth, see @tbl-config-entsoe-param and @tbl-config-entsoe-time.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "### Implementation of the Configuration"
      ],
      "id": "2840eb51"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: code-notebook-entsoe\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "from spotforecast2_safe.data import Period\n",
        "from spotforecast2_safe.manager.configurator.config_entsoe import ConfigEntsoe\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Initialize configuration\n",
        "config = ConfigEntsoe(\n",
        "    api_country_code=\"DE\",\n",
        "    periods=[\n",
        "        Period(name='daily', n_periods=12, column='hour', input_range=(1, 24))\n",
        "    ],\n",
        "    lags_consider=[1, 2, 24],\n",
        "    train_size=TRAIN_SIZE,\n",
        "    end_train_default=END_TRAIN_DEFAULT,\n",
        "    delta_val=DELTA_VAL,\n",
        "    predict_size=PREDICT_SIZE,\n",
        "    refit_size=7,\n",
        "    random_state=42,\n",
        "    n_hyperparameters_trials=50,\n",
        "    data_filename='interim/energy_load.csv'\n",
        ")"
      ],
      "id": "code-notebook-entsoe",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Hyperparameter Tuning (Model Selection)\n",
        "The `n_hyperparameters_trials` argument controls the model selection process. The system performs a randomized search over the hyperparameter space (defined in the library's internal search spaces for LGBM) to optimize validation metrics (CRPS/MAE) on the `delta_val` set.\n",
        "\n",
        "### API Reference: Configuration (General Parameters)\n",
        "\n",
        "| Argument | Type | Description | Value |\n",
        "| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n",
        "| `api_country_code` | `str` | ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 code (e.g., 'DE', 'FR'). | \"DE\"|\n",
        "| `random_state` | `int` | Seed for reproducibility. | `42` |\n",
        "| `n_hyperparameters_trials` | `int` | Number of trials for random search hyperparameter optimization. | `100` |\n",
        "| `data_filename` | `str` | Path to the interim merged data file. | `\"energy_load.csv\"` |\n",
        "\n",
        ": Configuration for Data Acquisition. General parameters. {#tbl-config-entsoe-param}\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "Based on the settings shown the last code snippet and in @tbl-config-entsoe-param, the general parameters of the  `ConfigEntsoe` object are instantiated as follows:\n",
        "\n",
        "* `api_country_code`: \"DE\", which means that the data will be downloaded from the ENTSO-E Transparency Platform for Germany.\n",
        "* `random_state`: 42. Reproducibility: The `random_state` is locked for all stochastic processes.\n",
        "* `n_hyperparameters_trials`: 50. If training is triggered, perform hyperparameter tuning using `n_hyperparameters_trials`.\n",
        "* `data_filename`: 'interim/energy_load.csv'\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "### API Reference: Configuration (Time-Related Parameters)\n",
        "\n",
        "| Argument | Type | Description | Value |\n",
        "| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n",
        "| `periods` | `List[Period]` | RBF specifications for cyclic features. | `[Period(name='daily', n_periods=12, column='hour', input_range=(1, 24))]`|\n",
        "| `lags_consider` | `List[int]` | Autoregressive lags | `[1, 2, 24]`|\n",
        "| `train_size` | `Timedelta` | Historical window used for training, here `TRAIN_SIZE` | `pd.Timedelta(days=365*3)` |\n",
        "| `end_train_default` | `str` | Default end date for training period (ISO format), here `END_TRAIN_DEFAULT`. | `END_TRAIN_DEFAULT` |\n",
        "| `delta_val` | `Timedelta` | Size of the validation set in days used for model selection, here `DELTA_VAL`. | `pd.Timedelta(days=14)` |\n",
        "| `predict_size` | `int` | Forecasting horizon (hours), here `PREDICT_SIZE`. | `PREDICT_SIZE` |\n",
        "| `refit_size` | `int` | Maximum age (in days) of a model before retraining is forced.  | `7` |\n",
        ": Configuration for Data Acquisition. Time-related parameters. {#tbl-config-entsoe-time}\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "Based on the settings shown the last code snippet and in @tbl-config-entsoe-param and @tbl-config-entsoe-time, the `ConfigEntsoe` object is instantiated as follows:\n",
        "\n",
        "* `periods`: [Period(name='daily', n_periods=12, column='hour', input_range=(1, 24))], so that smoothed 2-hour cyclical features are generated. We utilize Radial Basis Functions (RBF) to capture seasonality. A critical design choice is the resolution of the Daily period: 12 periods are used for the 24-hour daily cycle (instead of 24).  This effectively provides a 2-hour resolution, acting as a smoothing filter that reduces noise while halving the dimensionality of the feature space.\n",
        "The default `periods` are deliberately chosen to balance temporal resolution with model complexity (e.g., `daily` uses `n_periods=12` to smooth hourly noise while reducing dimensionality).\n",
        "* `lags_consider`: [1, 2, 24], so that the lags of 1 hour, 2 hours and 24 hours are considered.\n",
        "* `train_size`: `pd.Timedelta(days=365*3)`, so that the training data is 3 years old. Since the downloaded data is from `START_DOWNLOAD` to `END_DOWNLOAD`, the training data is from `START_DOWNLOAD` to `END_DOWNLOAD - pd.Timedelta(days=168)`.\n",
        "* `end_train_default`: `END_TRAIN_DEFAULT`, this is the cutoff timestamp separating training and testing data. Critical: it must leave enough future data for the full prediction horizon (`168h`).\n",
        "* `delta_val`: pd.Timedelta(days=14)\n",
        "* `predict_size`: `PREDICT_SIZE`. Determines the full forecast horizon (`predict_size * refit_size`).\n",
        "* `refit_size`: 7. If a trained model exists and is younger than `refit_size` days, skip training (unless `force=True`).\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "This `config` object is then injected into the two instances of the `ForecasterRecursiveModel`, guaranteeing that the trained model perfectly matches the intended experimental design.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Model Orchestration & Training\n",
        "\n",
        "To ensure safety-critical consistency, we define wrapper classes that inject the configuration directly into the model instances. The training process effectively manages the model lifecycle.\n",
        "The `handle_training` function saves the best-performing model to the artifact store.\n",
        "\n",
        "### API Reference of the Model Orchestration & Training\n",
        "\n",
        "The API Reference of the Model Orchestration & Training is shown in @tbl-model-entsoe.\n",
        "\n",
        "| Component | Type | Arguments | Description |\n",
        "| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n",
        "| `handle_training` | Function | `model_class` (Type)<br>`model_name` (str)<br>`force` (bool)<br>`data_filename` (str) | Orchestrates the training/retraining lifecycle. |\n",
        "| `ForecasterRecursive` | Class | `estimator`<br>`lags` | Base class for recursive multi-step forecasting. |\n",
        "\n",
        ": Model Orchestration & Training {#tbl-model-entsoe}\n",
        "\n",
        "### Implementation of the Model Orchestration & Training\n",
        "\n",
        "Define Config-Aware Wrappers:"
      ],
      "id": "15842ed4"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: code-notebook-entsoe-usage-wrapper\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "from spotforecast2_safe.manager.models.forecaster_recursive_lgbm import (ForecasterRecursiveLGBM as _ForecasterRecursiveLGBMBase)\n",
        "from spotforecast2.manager.trainer_full import handle_training\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Define Config-Aware Wrappers\n",
        "class ForecasterRecursiveLGBM(_ForecasterRecursiveLGBMBase):\n",
        "    \"\"\"LGBM forecaster with injected production config.\"\"\"\n",
        "    def __init__(self, iteration: int, lags: int = 12, **kwargs):\n",
        "        kwargs.setdefault(\"periods\", config.periods)\n",
        "        kwargs.setdefault(\"country_code\", config.API_COUNTRY_CODE)\n",
        "        kwargs.setdefault(\"random_state\", config.random_state)\n",
        "        kwargs.setdefault(\"end_dev\", config.end_train_default)\n",
        "        kwargs.setdefault(\"train_size\", config.train_size)\n",
        "        kwargs.setdefault(\"delta_val\", config.delta_val)\n",
        "        kwargs.setdefault(\"predict_size\", config.predict_size)\n",
        "        kwargs.setdefault(\"refit_size\", config.refit_size)\n",
        "        super().__init__(iteration=iteration, lags=lags, **kwargs)"
      ],
      "id": "code-notebook-entsoe-usage-wrapper",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "These wrapper class (`ForecasterRecursiveLGBM`) implements a Safety Injection Pattern. By automatically pulling parameters from the global `config` object during initialization, they guarantee that:\n",
        "\n",
        "1.  Configuration Integrity: The model cannot be initialized with ad-hoc parameters that conflict with the experimental design (e.g., matching `predict_size` and `refit_size`).\n",
        "2.  Simplified Orchestration: The training function (`entsoe_train`) does not need to accept or pass 20+ configuration arguments, reducing the risk of wiring errors.\n",
        "3.  Encapsulation: The model carries its own configuration context, ensuring that any internal refitting or prediction operations remain consistent with the global policy.\n",
        "\n",
        "The LGBM model:\n"
      ],
      "id": "9ac2f84f"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: get_params_lgbm\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "model_lgbm   = ForecasterRecursiveLGBM(iteration=1)\n",
        "pprint.pprint(model_lgbm.get_params())"
      ],
      "id": "get_params_lgbm",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Define Training Orchestrator:"
      ],
      "id": "6a680ac5"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: code-notebook-entsoe-training-orchestrator\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "def entsoe_train(model=\"lgbm\", force=False):\n",
        "    model_map = {\"lgbm\": ForecasterRecursiveLGBM}\n",
        "    \n",
        "    if model not in model_map:\n",
        "        logger.error(f\"Unknown model: {model}\")\n",
        "        return\n",
        "\n",
        "    logger.info(f\"Initiating training pipeline for {model}...\")\n",
        "    handle_training(\n",
        "        model_class=model_map[model],\n",
        "        model_name=model,\n",
        "        force=force,\n",
        "        data_filename=config.data_filename,\n",
        "        end_dev=config.end_train_default,\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    logger.info(f\"Training pipeline completed for {model}.\")"
      ],
      "id": "code-notebook-entsoe-training-orchestrator",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Note on explicit `end_dev` passage\n",
        "\n",
        "When `end_dev` is `None` (default), `handle_training` calculates the training cutoff based on the *latest available data* (minus 1 day). This behavior overrides the `end_train_default` (''2024-12-31 00:00+00:00') defined in the configuration, even if the model wrapper class sets it as a default.\n",
        "We explicitly pass `end_dev=config.end_train_default` to `handle_training` in the `entsoe_train` function. This forces the training orchestrator to respect the configuration, ensuring the model is trained with the correct cutoff date and leaving sufficient future data for validation and metric computation.\n",
        "\n",
        "Execute Training:"
      ],
      "id": "c579a035"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "cache": false
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: code-notebook-entsoe-execution\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "entsoe_train(force=True)"
      ],
      "id": "code-notebook-entsoe-execution",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
