      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Execution & Effects of Model Orchestration & Training\n",
        "\n",
        "The `entsoe_train` command (via `handle_training`) triggers a robust, state-aware training pipeline with the following effects:\n",
        "\n",
        "1.  **Smart Retraining Logic**:\n",
        "    *   **Check**: It first checks the artifact store for an existing model of the specified type.\n",
        "    *   **Validate**: If a model exists, it calculates its age. Retraining is triggered only if the model is **> 7 days old** (168 hours) or if `force=True`.\n",
        "    *   **Increment**: If retraining occurs, the iteration counter is incremented (e.g., `iteration 0` -> `iteration 1`).\n",
        "\n",
        "2.  **Data & Ranges**:\n",
        "    *   **Source**: Loads data from the file specified in `config.data_filename` (e.g., `energy_load.csv`).\n",
        "    *   **Training Window**: Uses data up to `end_dev`. By default, this is calculated as **one day before the last available data point** to ensure a full 24-hour hold-out set for immediate validation.\n",
        "\n",
        "3.  **Artifact Storage**:\n",
        "    *   **Location**: Models are serialized and saved to `~/spotforecast2_cache` (or the path in `SPOTFORECAST2_CACHE`).\n",
        "    *   **Format**: Files are named using the convention `{model_name}_forecaster_{n_iteration}.joblib` (e.g., `lgbm_forecaster_0.joblib`).\n",
        "    *   **Persistence**: These artifacts are persistent and can be loaded by prediction services without retraining.\n",
        "\n",
        "4.  **Side Effects**:\n",
        "    *   **Logging**: Emits INFO/ERROR logs detailing the training progress and any issues.\n",
        "    *   **File I/O**: Writes compressed `.joblib` files to disk.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "## Predictive Analytics & Visualization\n",
        "\n",
        "Predictions are returned as a comprehensive **Prediction Package** containing not just values, but metadata, metrics, and validation status, see @tbl-predict-entsoe.\n",
        "\n",
        "### API Reference\n",
        "\n",
        "| Component | Type | Arguments | Description |\n",
        "| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n",
        "| `get_model_prediction` | Function | `model_name` (str) | Loads the production model and executes `package_prediction`. Returns a dict with keys: `predictions`, `metrics`, `validation_passed`. |\n",
        "| `make_plot` | Function | `prediction_package` (dict) | Generates an interactive Plotly visualization from the prediction package. |\n",
        "\n",
        ": Predictive Analytics & Visualization {#tbl-predict-entsoe}\n",
        "\n",
        "### Implementation of the Predictive Analytics & Visualization"
      ],
      "id": "40ba0da5"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: code-notebook-entsoe-usage-predict\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
