        "\n",
        "## Training, Tuning, and Prediction Strategies\n",
        "\n",
        "In production environments, there are different approaches to applying the models depending on computational constraints and performance requirements. Here we document and compare three distinct approaches using the same underlying dataset and configuration.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Approach 1: Without Training and Tuning (Lazy Fitting)\n",
        "\n",
        "By default, executing predictions via the `spotforecast2_safe` pipeline against an untrained configuration instantiates the base model recursively. During the very first `predict()` invocation, it detects the lack of a pre-fitted estimator and performs a \"lazy\" fit using the absolute default hyperparameters on the fly without persisting them via `joblib`. \n",
        "\n",
        "This represents the absolute fastest development cycle but lacks optimization."
